</a>.)</p>

<br class="Q04">
<!-- field-end:sourcecredit -->
<!-- field-start:notes -->

<a name="miscellaneous-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:miscellaneous-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">
<strong>Editorial Notes</strong>
</h4>
<!-- field-end:miscellaneous-note -->

<a name="referenceintext-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:referenceintext-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">References in Text</h4>

<p class="note-body">The Rehabilitation Act of 1973, referred to in subsec. (a)(1), (2)(C)(i), is <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=87&page=355" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="93" isPrivate="false" number="112">Pub. L. 93&ndash;112,</pLaw> Sept. 26, 1973, <statuteAtLarge page="355" volume="87">87 Stat. 355</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, which is classified principally to <span onclick="openDocument('', '29', '16'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 16 (&sect;701 et seq.) of Title 29</span>, Labor. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under <span onclick="openDocument('701', '29', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 701 of Title 29</span> and Tables.</p>
<!-- field-end:referenceintext-note -->

<a name="priorprovisions-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:priorprovisions-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Prior Provisions</h4>

<p class="note-body">Prior section 3117 was renumbered <span onclick="openDocument('5317', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 5317 of this title</span>.</p>
<!-- field-end:priorprovisions-note -->

<a name="amendment-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:amendment-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Amendments</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<b>2023</b>-Subsec. (a)(2)(C). <pLaw congress="117" isPrivate="false" number="333">Pub. L. 117&ndash;333,</pLaw> &sect;14(c)(1), substituted "this subparagraph" for "this clause".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (b)(1). <pLaw congress="117" isPrivate="false" number="333">Pub. L. 117&ndash;333,</pLaw> &sect;14(c)(2)(A), substituted "ensure" for "insure".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (b)(2). <pLaw congress="117" isPrivate="false" number="333">Pub. L. 117&ndash;333,</pLaw> &sect;14(c)(2)(B), substituted "paragraph" for "clause" in two places.</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>2006</b>-Subsec. (b)(1). <pLaw congress="109" isPrivate="false" number="233">Pub. L. 109&ndash;233</pLaw> substituted "section 4(b)(1)" for "section 8" and "633(b)(1)" for "633(b)".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>2002</b>-Subsec. (a)(2)(B). <pLaw congress="107" isPrivate="false" number="288">Pub. L. 107&ndash;288</pLaw> amended subpar. (B) generally. Prior to amendment, subpar. (B) read as follows: "utilization of the services of disabled veterans outreach program specialists under <span onclick="openDocument('4103A', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 4103A of this title</span>; and".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1996</b>-Subsec. (a)(1). <pLaw congress="104" isPrivate="false" number="275">Pub. L. 104&ndash;275</pLaw> inserted "rated at 10 percent or more" after "disability".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1991</b>-<pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(a), renumbered <span onclick="openDocument('1517', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 1517 of this title</span> as this section.</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (a)(1). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="54">Pub. L. 102&ndash;54,</pLaw> &sect;14(c)(4)(A), inserted "(<span onclick="openDocument('701', '29', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">29 U.S.C. 701 et seq.</span>)" after "1973".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (a)(2)(B). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(c)(1), substituted "4103A" for "2003A".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (a)(2)(C)(v). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="54">Pub. L. 102&ndash;54,</pLaw> &sect;14(c)(4)(B), struck out second period at end.</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (b)(2). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(c)(1), substituted "3104(a)" for "1504(a)".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1989</b>-Subsecs. (a)(1), (2)(C), (b). <pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237</pLaw> substituted "Secretary" for "Administrator" wherever appearing.</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1988</b>-Subsec. (a)(2)(C). <pLaw congress="100" isPrivate="false" number="689">Pub. L. 100&ndash;689</pLaw> struck out "and" at end of subcl. (iii), substituted "available, and" for "available" in subcl. (iv), and added subcl. (v).</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1981</b>-Subsec. (b)(1). <pLaw congress="97" isPrivate="false" number="72">Pub. L. 97&ndash;72</pLaw> inserted provision requiring the Administrator to assist veterans in securing, as appropriate, a loan under subchapter IV of <span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '37'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 37</span> of this title.</p>

<br class="Q04">
<!-- field-end:amendment-note -->
<!-- field-start:miscellaneous-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">
<strong>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</strong>
</h4>
<!-- field-end:miscellaneous-note -->

<a name="effectivedate-amendment-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:effectivedate-amendment-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 1981 Amendment</h4>

<p class="note-body">Amendment by <pLaw congress="97" isPrivate="false" number="72">Pub. L. 97&ndash;72</pLaw> effective at end of 180-day period beginning on Nov. 3, 1981, see section 305 of <pLaw congress="97" isPrivate="false" number="72">Pub. L. 97&ndash;72,</pLaw> set out as an Effective Date note under <span onclick="openDocument('3741', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 3741 of this title</span>.</p>
<!-- field-end:effectivedate-amendment-note -->
<!-- field-start:effectivedate-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date</h4>

<p class="note-body">Section effective Apr. 1, 1981, see section 802(a)(1) of <pLaw congress="96" isPrivate="false" number="466">Pub. L. 96&ndash;466,</pLaw> set out as a note under <span onclick="openDocument('3100', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 3100 of this title</span>.</p>
<!-- field-end:effectivedate-note -->
<!-- field-end:notes -->





